      "repair_reason": "No automated repair is needed; the remaining blocker is contributor real behavior proof and normal maintainer review.; Cleared: The merge-ref diff only changes a local TypeScript model-selection helper and does not touch secrets, dependencies, CI, install, or code execution surfaces. (sha=bfa3640ad11adcdeac1e95a0beb54ccb81f896c6)",
      "review_summary": "The PR changes model catalog metadata construction so `provider/*` entries in `agents.defaults.models` are skipped when collecting aliases.\n\nPR surface: Source +4. Total +4 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. from source inspection, not from a live run: current main lets `buildModelCatalogMetadata` resolve a `provider/*` alias key even though the visibility parser and alias index already treat that key as a wildcard entry. I did not execute a current-main failing test in this read-only review.",
